<HEADLINE>
Agricultural Bank of China Opens Branch in HK
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 22 (Xinhua)
</P>
<P>
The Agricultural Bank of China opened its Hong Kong branch here today.
</P>
<P>
At the inauguration ceremony of the branch, Shi Jiliang, president of
the Agricultural Bank of China, said that the Hong Kong branch of the
bank will become a strategic base to woo future international business
and its service area covers Hong Kong, Taiwan, Macao and countries in
Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
Li Chuzhang, general manager of the Hong Kong Branch said that his
branch will operate assertively to promote Hong Kong's stability and
prosperity.
</P>
<P>
The Agricultural Bank of China set up its representative office in
Hong Kong in March, 1994 and last month it was granted a banking
license to set up a branch.
</P>
<P>
According to Li, the branch will sign an agreement tomorrow with the
Hong Kong-based Liu Chong Hing Group for lending 50 million HK dollars
(6.41 million US dollars) to the group.
</P>
<P>
He said that his branch also launched its 500 million HK dollar
floating rate certificates of deposit issue, and a signing ceremony
for increasing the issue size will be held soon.
</P>
<P>
At the opening reception, Li presented a 300,000 HK dollar check as
its donation to the Hong Kong Council of Early Childhood Education and
Services.
</P>
<P>
As one of China's four largest commercial banks, the Agricultural Bank
of China has more than 58,000 banking offices in operation. It has set
up a branch in Singapore and representative offices in London and
Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
In another development, the Industrial and Commercial Bank of China
also opened a branch in Hong Kong on November 20.
</P>
